#
# Custom recipe: SGLang main @ 3a1417a (post-v0.5.13) + SM121 sgl-kernel patches
#                + Gemma-4 NVFP4 source patch + DiffusionGemma dLLM (unmerged #28054).
#
# Tag: xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.14-gemmadiffusion-sm121
#
# THE UNIFIED GEMMA-4 IMAGE. Serves ALL five Gemma-4 profiles off one build:
#   - BF16 + FROZEN_KV_MTP (google/gemma-4-31B-it, google/gemma-4-26B-A4B-it)
#   - NVFP4 (nvidia/Gemma-4-31B-IT-NVFP4, nvidia/Gemma-4-26B-A4B-NVFP4)
#   - DiffusionGemma dLLM (nvidia/diffusiongemma-26B-A4B-it-NVFP4)
#
# WHY FORWARD-PINNED TO 3a1417a (main, 2026-06-12) INSTEAD OF THE v0.5.13 TAG:
#   1. FROZEN_KV_MTP fix. v0.5.13 (2026-06-11) shipped a short-lived BROKEN
#      FrozenKVMTPCudaGraphRunner — Gemma-4 BF16 MTP dies at boot with
#      "'NoneType' object has no attribute 'target_token_to_kv_pool'"
#      (kv_context is None). PR #28081 (merged 2026-06-12, commit 3a1417a) folds
#      that runner onto the shared DecodeCudaGraphRunner base and fixes it. The
#      PR diff does NOT apply onto the v0.5.13 tag (the crashing file diverged),
#      so we pin the source forward to the commit that has it natively.
#   2. Cleaner DiffusionGemma bake. PR #28054 is authored against main; baking it
#      onto the v0.5.13 TAG was main-vs-tag (drift risk on scheduler.py /
#      server_args.py / forward_batch_info.py). On this main-ahead base it is
#      main-vs-main (~same day) → much cleaner apply.
#   3. EAGLE v1 is still present at 3a1417a (removed later by #28129/#28133,
#      2026-06-13) — we pin BEFORE that removal to minimise drift; we don't need
#      it. To include the EAGLE-v1 cleanup, bump SGLANG_REF to
#      27ba13358eebcc05e494596706c2ac63ce00fb82.
#
# ⚠️  FIRST-CONTACT / main-ahead build — NOT a tagged release. Main risk: the
#     SM121 sgl-kernel source patches (always_source_patches: sgl-kernel-sm121
#     .patch et al.) were validated against the v0.5.13 tag. One day of main
#     drift may shift the sgl-kernel C++ source (nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh /
#     CMakeLists). The in-container `patch --dry-run` gates this — if it FAILS,
#     regenerate the sgl-kernel patch against 3a1417a before this recipe builds.
#
# The filename contains "gemma4" → build_sm121_image.sh applies the gemma4-NVFP4
# source patch (#22928 geglu-nan-clamp; inert on dense BF16, needed by NVFP4
# Gemma). The diffusiongemma Dockerfile patch anchors AFTER the gemma4 block, so
# this *gemma4* variant is required.
#
# Patches stacked (both still OPEN upstream):
#   - sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch (PR #22928) — Gemma-4 GeGLU + FP4
#     block-scale NaN clamp (NVFP4 path; inert on BF16).
#   - sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch (PR #28054) — dLLM Gemma4Renoise +
#     gemma4_diffusion encoder-decoder model + diffusion_gemma processor.
#     Auf 0/entfernen, sobald #28054 im gepinnten SGLANG_REF enthalten ist.
#
# ⚠️  TRANSFORMERS: PR #28054 bumpt im pyproject transformers 5.8.1 → 5.11.0;
#     dieser Hunk ist im Source-Patch GESTRIPPT (sglang --no-deps; transformers
#     separat via TRANSFORMERS_VERSION). Falls DiffusionGemma mit AutoConfig-/
#     Modeling-Fehler nicht lädt: TRANSFORMERS_VERSION hier auf 5.11.0 heben.
#
DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
TARGET=runtime

BASE_IMAGE=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132

# 0.6.13 (stable, released 2026-06-24; was 0.6.13rc2 — stable carries the same
# rc2 content). NB: flashinfer-attn stays UNUSABLE for Gemma4 (SGLang allowlist:
# trtllm_mha | triton | intel_xpu), so the PR #3576 head_dim=512 work is moot for
# Gemma attention; the bump only matters for the NVFP4 quant kernels.
FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.13

# 2026-06-20: auf 5.11.0 gehoben — 5.8.0 kennt model_type `diffusion_gemma` nicht
# (transformers CONFIG_MAPPING KeyError → "does not recognize this architecture" bei
# AutoConfig.from_pretrained; trust_remote_code hilft nicht, da das NVFP4-Repo keine
# auto_map/Remote-Config mitliefert). 5.11.0 ist die von PR #28054 gepinnte Version,
# in der die diffusion_gemma-Config nativ registriert ist. Betrifft das UNIFIED-Image
# → autoregressive Gemma-4-Profile (BF16/NVFP4/FROZEN_KV_MTP) auf 5.11.0 neu verifizieren.
TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=5.11.0

KERNELS_VERSION=0.12.3

# main-ahead pin (post-v0.5.13, 2026-06-12). 40-hex SHA → build clones + checks
# out the commit. SGLANG_VERSION is a dev string >= 0.5.12 so the build SKIPS the
# Gemma-4 MTP cherry-pick (#24436 is native here; re-applying would fail).
SGLANG_VERSION=0.5.14.dev20260612
SGLANG_REF="3a1417a0c16cde6ab89922b6908c74ab32a791bb"
# Alt — "all three spec PRs" incl. EAGLE-v1 removal (#28129/#28133), 2026-06-13:
# SGLANG_REF="27ba13358eebcc05e494596706c2ac63ce00fb82"

# Main-ahead sgl-kernel patch variant. Between v0.5.13 and 3a1417a sgl-kernel
# refactored the mscclpp link (dropped mscclpp_static from the common_ops_sm90/
# sm100 link lines + removed the mscclpp-build block), which drifts
# sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch (Hunk #3 FAILED at 398). This flag makes
# build_sm121_image.sh install the "-mainahead" patch variants (regenerated
# against 3a1417a) under the canonical names, while the v0.5.13 recipes keep
# the originals. Drop it if SGLANG_REF moves back to a tagged release.
SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1

# DiffusionGemma dLLM runtime — upstream PR #28054 (OPEN). Gated dockerfile-
# diffusiongemma.patch in build_sm121_image.sh::apply_patches (Schritt 2e).
APPLY_DIFFUSIONGEMMA_PR28054=1

IMAGE_TAG=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.14-gemmadiffusion-sm121
